-- Brooklyn Nets Hand NBA Champion Miami Heat Second Straight Loss
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2013-11-02T04:11:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-02/brooklyn-nets-hand-nba-champion-miami-heat-second-straight-loss.html
Paul Pierce  and  Joe Johnson  scored 19
points each as the Brooklyn Nets defeated the Miami Heat 101-100, sending the two-time National Basketball Association
champions to their second straight defeat.  The Nets broke a 13-game losing streak against Miami by
building an 11-point lead heading into the fourth quarter and
then holding on as the Heat made a late run.  LeBron James led Miami (1-2) with 26 points, seven rebounds
and six assists. Dwyane Wade added 21 points for the Heat.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rob Gloster in San Francisco at 
